New York Zip Codes 2020

At 54,556 square miles, New York is the 27th largest state in America. Administratively New York is divided into 7,384 cities and towns and 62 counties. The population in 2013 was 19,651,127 according to the United States Census, making it the 3rd most populous state in America.

As of January 2014, the state has roughly 2,158 zip codes, which are listed below with the respective city, town, village or location name as well as the area code. The capital is Albany (2012 population: 97,904) and the largest city is New York City (2012 population: 8,336,697).
